ospectors" : colonial contact zones and the eradication of African 'artisanal' miners -- Refusing the "white man's burden" : investing in colour-blind mining in post-apartheid South Africa -- Conclusion : imagining decolonized relations.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="520"><subfield code="a">Draws on colonial, postcolonial, and critical race theory to examine the racialized distribution of power that underpins Canadian mining in several African countries and reveal a colonialist mindset that legitimizes extraction through neo-liberal legal frameworks and a national myth of a humane, enlightened global actor.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="596"><subfield code="a">8 23 28</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2="0" tag="650"><subfield code="a">Mineral industries</subfield><subfield code="x">Social aspects</subfield><subfield code="z">Africa.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2="0" tag="650"><subfield code="a">Mineral industries</subfield><subfield code="x">Economic aspects</subfield><subfield code="z">Africa.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2="0" tag="650"><subfield code="a">Mining corporations</subfield><subfield code="z">Africa.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2="0" tag="650"><subfield code="a">Mining corporations</subfield><subfield code="z">Canada.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2="0" tag="650"><subfield code="a">Miners</subfield><subfield code="z">Africa</subfield><subfield code="x">Social conditions.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2="0" tag="651"><subfield code="a">Africa</subfield><subfield code="x">Race relations.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="926"><subfield code="a">HD 9506 A372 B88 2015</subfield><subfield code="w">LC</subfield><subfield code="c">1</subfield><subfield code="i">34917001376032</subfield><subfield code="d">11/28/2015</subfield><subfield code="l">ON_SHELF</subfield><subfield code="m">KEYANO</subfield